nography challenge prevailing understandings of secularity and religion, offering critical insight into current debates about immigration and national belonging.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-SA 3.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520974401zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520974401zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520974401/original  a978-3-11-069041-5 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0 EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-GOA